benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods/{paymentMethodId}/setDefault - Set the default payment method

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful setting of default payment method with various parameters and headers.
Non-Existing Resource: Scenarios handle non-existent account and payment method IDs with appropriate error responses.
Concurrency Issues: Scenarios test concurrent requests and ensure only one payment method is set as default.
Invalid Data Types: Scenarios cover invalid UUID formats and injection attacks, ensuring proper error responses.
Authorization: Scenarios ensure unauthorized access is handled correctly with 401 responses.
gaps: Partial Update: No explicit scenarios to ensure partial updates are rejected unless allowed.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover how the system handles multiple requests in a short time.
recommendations: Add tests to explicitly verify that partial updates are rejected unless allowed.
Include rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure the system handles multiple requests in a short time appropriately.
